{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_126","type":"agent_message","text":"The full targeted `test` task no longer fails with missing-registration errors. It now dies in the native test executable with a startup segfault in `java.io.UnixFileSystem.initIDs`, which is a different regression and likely tied to the new test-isolation approach rather than missing metadata itself."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_127","type":"agent_message","text":"The new isolation strategy itself is causing the next problem: both the trace executable and the full native test binary now crash at startup, and the crash signature points at filesystem-native library initialization. I’m replacing the `URLClassLoader`-based isolation with an in-memory child-first loader that reads class bytes from resources, which should preserve the test isolation without dragging in the problematic filesystem path."}}
