{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_129","type":"agent_message","text":"I’m validating the next approach before patching: an in-memory loader would avoid the filesystem crash, but it only works if class bytes are actually available at runtime in the native executable. If they aren’t, the safer fallback is to keep everything in the system loader and explicitly reset the specific Byte Buddy static state that the unsafe-factory test contaminates."}}
